   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Educate the Whole Girl &amp; Her Community in Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In pursuit of Fallen Peace Corps Volunteer Elizabeth Bowers&apos; (Beth&apos;s) dream, our small, all-volunteer organization enabled a paradigm shift in attitude toward  women&apos;s education in remote NW Zambia.  By building a Memorial Library, the first pre-school, and Phase I of a secondary school (two 3-classroom blocks, two teachers&apos; houses, and a girls&apos; lavatory), we empower hundreds of girls to further their education and attain their dreams.  Now Phase II:  a 3-classroom block and a teacher&apos;s house.</narrative>
  </description>
